A mortgage is a loan used to purchase real estate, where the property serves as collateral. The borrower makes a down payment and then repays the loan amount, plus interest, over a set term (typically 15 to 30 years). Monthly payments include principal and interest, and may also cover property taxes and insurance. If the borrower fails to repay, the lender can foreclose on the property.
